This paper deals with distributed computing, which is a core topic in computer science and falls under the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category. The paper also deals with channel noise, which is a topic in information theory and falls under the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. The paper discusses the impact of an adversary on the protocol, which is a topic in computer security and falls under the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The paper also deals with communication over private point-to-point channels, which is a topic in computer networks and falls under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the protocol, which is a topic in control theory and falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
